  "text": "where M : R s → R s×s is the positive definite inertia matrix and V : R s → R is the potential energy function. It is assumed that position y is measurable and we want to estimate velocityẏ via the estimation of momenta x and the relationẏ = M −1 (y)x. It will be shown that if the dynamics can be rendered linear in momenta (velocities) via a change of coordinates then Assumptions 1 and 2 of the paper are satisfied. Moreover, the resulting reparameterisation is linear, that is, of the form [CITATION_1] , and the PE condition (22) is trivially satisfied, hence the set U is the whole input space. These systems, referred as PLvCC, have been studied in [CITATION_2] and they have been characterised via the solvability of a PDE-see also [CITATION_3] for an intrinsic characterisation of the class.",
